			<tr>
			<td>45602</td><td>User Story: Ex-Works (EXW) Checkout</td><td>Title: Checkout with Ex-Works Shipping Option

As a customer
I want to select Ex-Works (EXW) as the shipping method during checkout
So that I can arrange pickup and shipping of the goods directly from the seller’s location.


Description

Ex-Works (EXW) allows the buyer to take full responsibility for shipping, customs clearance, and delivery from the seller’s warehouse or store location. During checkout, the user can select EXW instead of standard shipping options.


Acceptance Criteria


Shipping Method Visibility
EXW option is displayed in the shipping methods section if the product supports EXW.The option clearly states: “Buyer arranges pickup from seller location.”
Seller Location Display
When EXW is selected, the seller’s pickup address and contact details are shown.
Shipping Cost
Shipping cost is set to 0 when EXW is selected.Order summary updates dynamically after selection.
Pickup Acknowledgment
User must check a confirmation box:&quot;“I understand that I am responsible for pickup, shipping, and customs clearance.”
&quot;
Order Confirmation
Order status is marked as:
Pending Pickup after successful payment.
Seller receives notification that order is EXW.
Notifications
Buyer receives confirmation email including:
Seller pickup addressContact informationOrder reference number

Admin Panel
Admin can see shipping type = EXW in order details.Admin can filter orders by shipping method (EXW).


