			<tr>
			<td>45642</td><td>[Admin-1] User Story: Settings Management</td><td>As an Admin
I want to manage platform settings from the Settings page
So that I can control system configurations from one place.


 Description

The Settings screen contains multiple setting cards/sections where the Admin can:


Update general platform informationConfigure system optionsToggle activation statusEdit configurable valuesSave changes per section

Each settings block appears as a separate card with editable fields and a Save button.


✅ Acceptance Criteria

1️⃣ Access Control


Only Admin users can access the Settings page.Unauthorized users cannot view the page.


2️⃣ Editable Settings Sections


Settings are displayed in grouped cards.Each card contains:
Input fields (text / number).Toggle buttons (Enable / Disable).Status indicators (Active / Inactive badges).Save button for that section.



3️⃣ Field Behavior


Input fields:
Support inline validation.Show error messages for invalid values.
Toggle buttons:
Change status visually (Active / Inactive).Update value on save.
Disabled settings appear visually different from active ones.


4️⃣ Save Action


Clicking Save:
Validates all fields in the section.Shows loading state.Displays success message on success.Displays error message if request fails.
Changes persist after page refresh.
