			<tr>
			<td>46360</td><td>Application link fields become mandatory when cleared and prevent saving phone and email</td><td>Description:
When the user clicks on any Application Link field and deletes the existing data, the system incorrectly treats the field as mandatory. As a result, the user is unable to save updates made to other fields such as Phone or Email unless the application link field is filled again.
However, these link fields are supposed to be optional, so the form should allow saving even if they are left empty

Actual Result:


The application link field becomes mandatory after deleting the data.The system does not allow saving the updated phone or email.

Expected Result:


Application link fields should remain optional even if the data is deleted.The user should be able to save phone and email successfully without filling the link fields.
